' #: A dance depicting {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|スサノオノミコト|12=draft|12=draft}} slaying the {{ill|Yamata no Orochi|ja|ヤマタノオロチ|12=draft|12=draft}}. # '''Kami Mukae (神迎)''' #: A dance in which {{ill|Izanagi|ja|イザナギ|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Izanami|ja|イザナミ|12=draft|12=draft}} are welcomed by Sarutahiko. # '''Kanzui Kagura (神髄神楽)''' #: A dance purifying the ritual grounds, invoking fire deities for protection. # '''Yunomisaki (湯の駈仙)''' #: A purification ritual for the sacred cauldron. # '''Yubō (湯棒)''' #: A sacred offering to the eight million gods. # '''Yugyōji (湯行事)''' #: Ritual purification of the hot springs, involving first fruits and fire-walking. # '''Sairyōsha (裁量者)''' #: The firekeeper overseeing the ritual grounds. # '''Norito (祝詞)''' #: Chanting of purification prayers. # '''Omoikane no Mikoto (思兼の命)''' #: A dance presided over by the god of wisdom at the celestial cave. # '''Shihō Oni (四方鬼)''' #: A dance featuring oni representing the four cardinal directions. # '''Kishin Taiji (鬼神退治)''' #: A sword dance symbolizing the vanquishing of evil spirits. # '''Futodama no Mikoto (太玉命)''' #: A dance offering the sacred sakaki tree from Mount Kagu. # '''Tamanooya no Mikoto (玉祖命)''' #: A ritual dance using bells and a fan. # '''Ishikoridome no Mikoto (石凝姥命)''' #: A dance presenting a mirror before the celestial cave. # '''Nagashiraha no Mikoto (長白羽命)''' #: A bow and arrow dance performed at the celestial cave. # '''Ame-no-Uzume no Mikoto (天鈿女命)''' #: A dance of joyful performance using bells and a fan. # '''Tajikarao no Mikoto (手力男命)''' #: A powerful dance symbolizing the opening of the celestial cave.
