== The Thirty-Three Kagura == {{section-stub}} # '''Ōbarai Kiyomibari (大祓清祓)''' #: Purification of the ritual grounds and kagura performers. # '''Ichiban Kagura (壱番神楽)''' #: The first kagura performed before the gods, from beginning to end. # '''Tebusa Kagura (手房神楽)''' #: A kagura performed with two stalks of bamboo, chanting the twelve zodiac signs; also called Sasa Kagura. # '''Hana Kagura (花神楽)''' #: A ritual where spiritual energy is scattered like flowers and delivered to the local {{ill|Ubusunagami|en|Ubusunagami|qid=Q1392097|lt=Ubusunagami|1=Ubusunagami}} [[Category:Wikidata no short description]] [[Category:Yasaka-jinja]] [[Category:Pages with 50+ untranslated japanese characters]] [[Category:Pages with 100+ untranslated japanese characters]]
